assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: sMedio, Inc. provides software development and services worldwide. The company offers multimedia and wireless connectivity solutions. It offers sMedio Face Detector, a face recognition solution; sMedio Emotion Recognition, a facial expression recognition solution; sMedio Gender Recognition and sMedio Age Recognition solutions, which estimates gender and age from a detected face; sMedio Motion Recognition that detects moving people in a video, and recognizes their motions as standing, sitting, walking, running, and falling; and sMedio Object Tracker, objects detection and tracking solution in a video. The company also provides sMedio IoT Gateway Solution, a gateway software for IoT devices; sMedio IoT Edge Device SDK, a software development solution for IoT edge devices; JS Backup, a backup tool; JS backup viewer, a photo viewer application; RiskFinder, a web service for vulnerability assessment on Android applications; tourbillon3, a HTML, BML, and IPTV based embedded browser; and Valution BD, a Blu-ray Disc playback software. In addition, it offers sMedio DTCP MOVE, an app for NAS system; sMedio True VR, a multimedia solution for virtual reality; sMedio True VR Sound, an engine to enable monaural sound to be 3D spatialize sound; sMedio pConnect for connecting the iOS/Android smartphone to PC; sMedio TV Suite for Android and Windows; sMedio TrueLink+ Hi-Res Edition, a multifunctional media player that enables Hi-res audio playback; and sMedio Remote Access Solutions for remote access servers and clients. sMedio, Inc. was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
